Authors: Binsar F., Eryanto E., Wahyudi I., Sugandi Y., Suroso J.S.
Title: Risk of invalidation of data in hospital information systems in Indonesia
Source title: Proceedings of 2020 International Conference on Information Management and Technology, ICIMTech 2020
Affiliations: BINUS Graduate Program - Master of Information Systems, Management Bina Nusantara University, Information Systems Management Department, Jakarta, 11480, Indonesia
Authors with affiliations: Binsar, F., BINUS Graduate Program - Master of Information Systems, Management Bina Nusantara University, Information Systems Management Department, Jakarta, 11480, Indonesia; Eryanto, E., BINUS Graduate Program - Master of Information Systems, Management Bina Nusantara University, Information Systems Management Department, Jakarta, 11480, Indonesia; Wahyudi, I., BINUS Graduate Program - Master of Information Systems, Management Bina Nusantara University, Information Systems Management Department, Jakarta, 11480, Indonesia; Sugandi, Y., BINUS Graduate Program - Master of Information Systems, Management Bina Nusantara University, Information Systems Management Department, Jakarta, 11480, Indonesia; Suroso, J.S., BINUS Graduate Program - Master of Information Systems, Management Bina Nusantara University, Information Systems Management Department, Jakarta, 11480, Indonesia
Abstract: Patient medical record data stored in hospital management information systems have become a necessity and demand for policymakers to obtain information quickly. The existence of this medical record can provide health profile information and medical history of the patients being treated. With this basis, doctors and medical staff can provide diagnoses, suggestions for actions to be taken as well as accuracy in determining the drug for patient consumption. However, medical records in the system at the hospital have not been packaged properly invalid data conditions, because the data collection and input processes were carried out by different officers. Not only the ability of officers to interact with information system modules but also discipline, accuracy, mastery of officers in the medical field as well as the ability to read manual documents to be re-entered into the information system. This research was carried out based on direct monitoring of the system used in several hospitals and found the existence of data invalidity in the information system that has the potential to become a risk that ultimately becomes a loss both for patients and for medical staff and hospital management. Allowing invalid data will be a threat that comes from within the hospital environment itself. © 2020 IEEE.
Author Keywords: Data validation; Electronic medical record; Health information system; Information system security; Risk management

Authors: Salampessy H., Tuhelelu A., Wahyudi I., Umanailo M.C.B.
Title: Banking servqual analysis of customer satisfaction (case study at Ambon branch BRI bank in Ambon City)
Source title: Proceedings of the International Conference on Industrial Engineering and Operations Management
Affiliations: Universitas Darussalam, Maluku, 97128, Indonesia; Department of Sociology, Faculty of Social and Political Sciences, Brawijaya University, East Java, Indonesia
Authors with affiliations: Salampessy, H., Universitas Darussalam, Maluku, 97128, Indonesia; Tuhelelu, A., Universitas Darussalam, Maluku, 97128, Indonesia; Wahyudi, I., Universitas Darussalam, Maluku, 97128, Indonesia; Umanailo, M.C.B., Department of Sociology, Faculty of Social and Political Sciences, Brawijaya University, East Java, Indonesia
Abstract: The purpose of this study is to analyze the quality of service (servqual) among others empirically testing the influence of Tangible, Reliability, Responsiveness, Assurance, and Empathy on Customer Satisfaction. The population in this study is BRI Ambon Branch customers in Ambon City. The sampling method used was purposive sampling with a total sample of 91 people to be studied. The analytical tool used is a Multiple Linear Regression. The results showed that the significant influence between Tangible on Customer Satisfaction, Reliability on Customer Satisfaction, Responsiveness on Customer Satisfaction, Assurance on Customer Satisfaction and Empathy on Customer Satisfaction either simultaneously or partially. © IEOM Society International.
Author Keywords: Customer satisfaction; Multiple linear regression; ServQual

Title: Experimental study of mobile number portability – Could it be a potential breakthrough in Indonesia telecommunication market?

Prof. TM Hanafiah, SH No.12, Medan, North Sumatera  20155, Indonesia
Abstract: This research emphasized on the moderation effect to customer knowledge which linked between MNP and switching attitudes. The result would led to the compositon domains, from call quality, customer complement, customer attachment, and corporate reputation on switching attitudes moderated by knowledge of MNP. Experimental method was excuted to 168 cellular card users in Indonesia. The experimental group further discrete into two catagories as 85 respondents with MNP knowledge and 83 respondents for control group. Analyzing the moderating model using multi-group PLS-SEM. The results demonstrate that the presence of moderation for knowledge of MNP did not affect significantly on switching attitudes for both groups. It indicated that the implementation of MNP will not interfere on the substantial ratio of customer switch to telecommunication industry in Indonesia. The originality of this study is by conducting the MNP experimental research in countries that have not applied MNP and adding switching attitudes with the moderation role from knowledge of MNP. © 2018, ASERS Publishing House. All rights reserved.
Author Keywords: Call quality; Corporate reputation; Customer attachment; Customer complement; Knowledge of MNP; Mobile number portability; Switching attitudes
